title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 1300 Stainless Steel Marine 12 Gauge Pump Shotgun (excellent condition)
postcontent:
Here is a rare Winchester Model 1300 Stainless Marine 12 Gauge Pump Action shotgun. The shotgun has an 18-1/2 inch barrel, front rifle sight with a silver bead, flip-up adjustable rear sight, 6+1 shot capacity, wood stock and forearm and is chambered for both 2-3/4 & 3 inch shells.

From the research I have done this shotgun sells for upwards of $800-$1,000 dollars so at $750 for one in pristine condition and having been fired less than 25 times this is an amazing deal. Being stainless steel this shotgun is rust proof, and makes an excellent addition to any boat or home.

This gun appears to have been manufactured in the mid 1980's at Winchester's New Haven Connecticut plant. These Winchester Model 1300 Marine’s have a Stainless barrel, magazine tube and a few other parts. The Stainless parts are nickel plated as well as the aluminum receiver, trigger group and most of the internals. The Stainless Marine was issued to the US Coast Guard and other maritime law enforcement agencies as well as the civilian market. These Winchester’s are rugged and very corrosion resistant.

This Stainless Steel Marine 12 Gauge Shotgun is in excellent condition. All the furniture appears to be in great shape. The pump forearm is in very good condition with no scratches or dents anywhere on the wood. The nickel finish on the stainless steel barrel is pristine. The bore is smooth and shinny and looks great and the receiver is in excellent condition. The finish is very reflective and the gun is in like new condition without a scratch.

title: For Sale:  Reloading Stuff
postcontent:
Hello. So this is the reloading setup I was putting together starting a few years ago but never got around to completing. I recently decided to focus on my pistols in indoor ranges much closer to where I live where they usually make you buy their ammo so reloading is kinda moot at this point. 

I have a Lee hand press kit # 90179
RCBS Hand Priming Tool #90200
RCBS 3- die carb TC Set 9mm Luger P/N 20515
RCBS F L Die Set .223 Rem P/N 11101

I'm also throwing in a bag full of once shot 223 brass consisting of about 125+ shells and a Redding Shell holder P/N 11006

None of it is used, all still in the box but the boxes have been all over the house over the years so the boxes are pretty tired. Perfect for someone that wants to try their hand at reloading but don't want to pay too much. 

I brought the price down a little because the last time I posted this there seemed to be interest from people not in the area and wanted me to ship it. It was fine except they were only offering like 10 bucks and sadly it would be a little more than that so hopefully this would make it a little more affordable for them. 
If you're local than I'm more than happy to meet you someplace public after work like a Fred Meyers parking lot or something. If I get contacted before work I can throw everything in my car and be ready to meet up as soon as I'm off. I'm working all over town this week so there's no telling if I'll be close or not but I never care if I have to drive. 

Everything goes, not splitting it up. Not interested in trades unless it's a Glock 21 in which case I also have enough cash to throw in....yeah it's a long shot but you never know. 

Now my spiel. The ad stays up as long as it remains unsold. I take it down as soon as I sell it. If I don't reply it's because I can't get to a computer or because there's one or more people that replied first. This doesn't mean I don't value your interest it's just the fairest way to run things. I accept on a first come-first serve basis but for the love of god please don't jerk me around. I'll even be hesitant if you told me I'd have to wait till the weekend because that means I could possibly get several people with cash in hand wanting to purchase and where does that leave me? I'll wait and piss off everyone that came after you. I'll go ahead and sell it to them and suddenly you think I'm an asshole and tell me why I suck over email. I mean I'll still be accommodating just please be serious.

And I've been jerked around enough to know a few buyers I should avoid. These people will also not get a response from me.

That's enough from me. Enjoy the lousy pics (zero interest in photography, I'm sorry). Look up the part numbers for more info. Like I said I never got the chance to get into reloading but I'll try to be as much help as I can.

Cheers
